<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="680" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1074,419,667]" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">
COMMENTS: This species may be distinguished from most of its congeners by the middle of the metaventrite densely punctate, lacking smooth mesal area, with distinct pubescence and foveiform impression in middle. It is also well characterized by the shape of the aedeagus and the internal sac lacking complex of sclerites and flagellum. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1980" box="[272,576,547,571]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudobironium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="680" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagiferum">
<emphasis box="[272,576,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">Pseudobironium plagiferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that shares a simple internal sac without a complex of sclerotized structures, differs drastically by the colour pattern of body, longer antennae with the antennomere IV about as long as two thirds of III, and by the shape of the parameres.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
