<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="680" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1074,805,957]" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">
COMMENTS: The description of this species was based on a single specimen from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[223,301,837,861]" name="Taiwan" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
”, lacking detailed locality data. Additional records from 
<collectingCountry box="[925,1003,837,861]" name="Taiwan" pageId="15" pageNumber="680">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
are in 
<bibRefCitation author="LOBL, I." box="[151,286,869,893]" pageId="15" pageNumber="680" pagination="199 - 207" refId="ref36313" refString="LOBL, I. 2011 b. Notes on some Taiwanese Scaphidiinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) described by Miwa and Mitono, with description of a new species and new records. Japanese Journal of systematic Entomology 17: 199 - 207." type="journal article" year="2011">Löbl, 2011b</bibRefCitation>
. This species may be easily distinguished from its congeners by the conspicuous colour pattern of the elytra, each having a large, well delimited black spot separated from elytral margins and sutural stria by bright reddish areas.
</paragraph>
